@ToDoApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5270

### Health check
GET {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/health
Accept: application/json

### List all tasks (newest run starts empty on a fresh DB)
GET {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks
Accept: application/json

### Create a task — capture the response so later requests can reuse its id
# @name createTask
POST {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Write the take-home README",
  "description": "Cover architecture and key decisions",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-30"
}

### Get the task just created (id pulled from the create response)
GET {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{createTask.response.body.id}}
Accept: application/json

### Update the task and mark it complete (PUT also toggles completion)
PUT {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{createTask.response.body.id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Write the take-home README",
  "description": "Cover architecture, key decisions, and trade-offs",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-30",
  "isCompleted": true
}

### Delete the task
DELETE {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{createTask.response.body.id}}

### 404 — a task that does not exist returns ProblemDetails
GET {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks/999999
Accept: application/json

### 400 — validation: blank title and missing due date return ProblemDetails
POST {{ToDoApi_HostAddress}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "   ",
  "description": "no title, no due date"
}

###
